<F P=100> INTERNATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<H3> <TI>   Butrus-Ghali Appoints UN Disarmament Conference Chief </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Butrus-Ghali Appoints UN Disarmament Conference Chief </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD0104064894 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 0602 GMT 1 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD0104064894 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS correspondent Boris Sitnikov] </F>
  [Text] United Nations April 1 TASS -- U.N. Secretary 
General Butrus Butrus-Ghali has appointed Vladimir Petrovskiy 
general secretary of the U.N. disarmament conference in Geneva, 
U.N. secretary general's official representative Joe Sills said 
here today. 
  Announcing this decision, Joe Sills said that after proper 
consultations with members of the disarmament conference, the 
U.N. secretary general has decisded to appoint director general 
of the U.N. branch in Geneva Vladimir Petrovskiy as disarmament 
conference general secretary, and also as his special 
representative at the conference. This decision comes into 
force immediately, Joe Sills said. 
  Joe Sills noted that Petrovskiy had been carrying out these 
duties on a temporary basis since December 5, 1993. Sills said 
that Petrovskiy will continue to carry out duties of the U.N. 
branch director general in Geneva. 

</TEXT>

